                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13564657" author="jpacker" created="Mon, 28 Jan 2013 20:38:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See issue description&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13584340" author="jcoveney" created="Fri, 22 Feb 2013 15:20:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you put this into RB?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13584607" author="kadeng" created="Fri, 22 Feb 2013 19:58:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why remove the choice of delimiter ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While the name correctly suggests that commas are used to delimit fields, many datasets use another delimiter for very good reasons.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13586393" author="jpacker" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2013 22:43:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Re-adds the choice of delimiter, and makes the &quot;header treatment&quot; argument the last one to maintain backwards compatibility. All unit-tests from the old CSVExcelStorage pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13586400" author="jpacker" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2013 22:46:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, I re-added the choice of delimiter. I&apos;m bothered by the fact that you have to explicitly state a &apos;,&apos; delimiter if you ever want to use the other parameters, but I agree in retrospect that it&apos;s not worth removing the feature entirely. The lastest patch should be completely backwards compatible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13589718" author="jcoveney" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 17:55:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you toss this into reviewboard?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13590589" author="jpacker" created="Fri, 1 Mar 2013 14:55:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed diff so it&apos;s from trunk instead of branch-0.11&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13590592" author="jpacker" created="Fri, 1 Mar 2013 14:56:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, I put it on reviewboard here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/9697/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/9697/&lt;/a&gt; . Sorry, I hadn&apos;t known what that was earlier.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13608029" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 20 Mar 2013 19:07:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you Jonathan P. for the patch! I made some comments to the RB.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13612710" author="jpacker" created="Mon, 25 Mar 2013 15:29:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated diff with code review changes (also updated on ReviewBoard). Thanks for taking a look at this and the fixed-width patch Cheolsoo.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13613488" author="cheolsoo" created="Tue, 26 Mar 2013 04:40:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Committed to trunk. Thanks Jonathan P!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that I got rid of all the ^M&apos;s in the following files while committing them:&lt;/p&gt;
